A Survey of the Usages of Deep Learning in Natural Language Processing

  Over the last several years, the field of natural language processing hasbeen propelled forward by an explosion in the use of deep learning models. Thissurvey provides a brief introduction to the field and a quick overview of deeplearning architectures and methods. It then sifts through the plethora ofrecent studies and summarizes a large assortment of relevant contributions.Analyzed research areas include several core linguistic processing issues inaddition to a number of applications of computational linguistics. A discussionof the current state of the art is then provided along with recommendations forfuture research in the field.

